@startuml
title HelloUpscaler Integration Guide

skinparam monochrome true
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam defaultTextAlignment left

start

:Goal;
note right
Integrate a didactic AMD FSR upscaler sample
into LightD3D12 as a separate example.
The sample must show:
- internal rendering
- motion vectors
- depth
- FSR dispatch
- final presentation
- ImGui controls
end note

:Step 1 - Prepare the solution;
note right
Files involved:
- C:/LightWeightD3D12/LightD3D12.sln
- C:/LightWeightD3D12/LightD3D12.FSR.props
- C:/LightWeightD3D12/samples/HelloUpscaler/HelloUpscaler.vcxproj

Reason:
The sample needs its own project and shared FSR
build configuration so the SDK can be enabled
without affecting unrelated samples.
end note

:Step 2 - Define the external dependency layout;
note right
Expected SDK layout:
- Kits/FidelityFX/api/include
- Kits/FidelityFX/upscalers/include
- Kits/FidelityFX/signedbin

Chosen linkage model:
- import .lib at link time
- DLLs copied for runtime

Why:
This matches the current AMD distribution model
and keeps SDK updates simple.
end note

:Step 3 - Expose the minimum native DX12 access;
note right
LightD3D12 exposes:
- native ID3D12Device
- native ID3D12Resource for textures
- native ID3D12GraphicsCommandList

Why:
AMD FSR DX12 entry points need real D3D12 objects.
end note

:Step 4 - Create a dedicated sample;
note right
Base idea:
Use HelloPostProcess as the structural reference.

Why:
It already demonstrates offscreen rendering,
resource transitions, compute dispatch,
and presentation.
end note

:Step 5 - Add sample state;
note right
Main structures added:
- OffscreenTargets
- FsrState
- PresentPushConstants
- AppState

Responsibilities:
- own internal render textures
- own FSR context lifetime
- store UI state
- carry current/previous frame data
end note

:Step 6 - Render the scene at internal resolution;
note right
The sample creates:
- sceneColor
- sceneDepth
- motionVectors
- upscaledOutput

Why:
Temporal upscalers need more than color.
They need depth and motion information to
reproject prior frame history correctly.
end note

:Step 7 - Add jittered projection;
note right
Each frame:
- query jitter phase count from FSR
- query jitter offset
- apply jitter to projection

Why:
Temporal reconstruction accumulates sub-pixel
detail over time, so the camera projection must
be intentionally shifted each frame.
end note

:Step 8 - Build the scene shaders;
note right
Scene vertex shader outputs:
- current jittered clip position
- current unjittered clip position
- previous unjittered clip position
- motion vector

Scene pixel shader outputs:
- shaded color
- motion vector target

Why:
The upscaler consumes motion vectors and depth
alongside the current frame color.
end note

:Step 9 - Create and maintain the FSR context;
note right
Lifecycle:
- compute desired internal resolution from quality mode
- create context when needed
- recreate on resize or mode changes
- destroy cleanly on shutdown

Important inputs:
- max render size
- max upscale size
- FSR flags
end note

:Step 10 - Dispatch AMD FSR;
note right
The dispatch stage maps LightD3D12 resources
to FSR DX12 resources and supplies:
- color
- depth
- motion vectors
- output UAV
- frame delta
- camera near/far/FOV
- reset flag

Why:
This is the actual temporal upscale pass.
end note

:Step 11 - Present the result;
note right
Presentation shader supports:
- final output
- split comparison
- difference heatmap
- center zoom

ImGui exposes:
- FSR on/off
- quality mode
- sharpening
- debug view
- FPS / frame time

Why:
The sample is didactic, so the user must be able
to inspect what changes when FSR is enabled.
end note

:Step 12 - Validate the first working path;
note right
Checks performed:
- compile solution
- launch sample
- verify the window stays alive
- confirm ImGui and FSR path run together
end note

:Step 13 - Investigate the runtime crash;
note right
Observed symptom:
The app closed shortly after launch.

Initial clue:
Windows Error Reporting pointed at ProcessMessage,
but that was not the root cause.

Debug method:
- collect Application Error event
- symbolize the offset
- run under cdb
end note

:Step 14 - Find the real cause;
note right
The first meaningful exception was a shader
compilation failure during CreatePresentPipeline.

Root cause:
In the presentation pixel shader, a local variable
was named "line".

Why it broke:
In HLSL, "line" is a reserved modifier,
so the shader failed to compile at startup.
end note

:Step 15 - Apply the minimal fix;
note right
Fix:
- rename "line" to "gridLine"

Result:
- shader compiles
- sample builds
- executable stays running

Why this matters:
This was the real blocker preventing startup.
end note

:Step 16 - Polish the sample for handoff;
note right
Final cleanup requested:
- keep shader text consistent
- move ImGui messages to English
- document the whole path in UML

Outcome:
The sample is easier to explain, maintain,
and demo.
end note

stop
@enduml
